34–1285","1259–1283":"1259–1283","–1305":"–1305","1190–Male":"1190–Deceased","1182–Female":"1182–Deceased","1190":"1190","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1182":"1182","1305":"1305","about 1208":"about 1208","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1212":"1212","1244":"1244","ABT 1234":"about 1234","1208":"1208","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","South Lyttleton,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","South Lyttleton, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lyttleton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Littleton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Littleton","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places, mostly in southwestern England, named in Old English as ‘small settlement’, from <i>lȳtel</i> ‘small’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":7,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":16,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry De Lyttleton was born about 1208, in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Lyttleton, was 20 and his mother, Alice Somery, was 27. He married Emma about 1234, in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1244, in Shropshire, England, at the age of 37."},"et":{"about 1208–1244":"umbes 1208–1244","1208–1244":"1208–1244","1212–Female":"1212–Surnud","1234–1285":"1234–1285","1259–1283":"1259–1283","–1305":"–1305","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1182–Female":"1182–Surnud","1190":"1190","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1182":"1182","1305":"1305","about 1208":"umbes 1208","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1212":"1212","1244":"1244","ABT 1234":"umbes 1234","1208":"1208","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","South Lyttleton,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","South Lyttleton, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1208–1244":"noin 1208–1244","1208–1244":"1208–1244","1212–Female":"1212–Kuollut","1234–1285":"1234–1285","1259–1283":"1259–1283","–1305":"–1305","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1182–Female":"1182–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1182":"1182","1305":"1305","about 1208":"noin 1208","1215":"1215","1259":"1259","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1212":"1212","1244":"1244","ABT 1234":"noin 1234","1208":"1208","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Eng